---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Offline FileSecure | DK App Tools"
  description="Offline FileSecure is a local-first Android file vault from DK App Tools."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Offline FileSecure</p>
      <h1>Private files. Stored locally. Protected clearly.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Offline FileSecure is a simple Android vault for files you do not want exposed.
        It is designed around local storage, clear protection, and no account requirement.
      </p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button" href="/privacy/offline-filesecure">Privacy Policy</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href="/support">Support</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Principles</p>
    <h2>Local-first by design.</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>No account</h3>
        <p>Offline FileSecure does not require an account to protect files on your device.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>No cloud upload</h3>
        <p>Files added to the vault are not uploaded to DK App Tools cloud servers.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>No ads</h3>
        <p>The app is built without ads, tracking SDKs, or analytics SDKs.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section">
    <p class="note">
      Import creates an encrypted copy inside the app. Your original file remains in
      its original location unless you delete it yourself. Export creates a decrypted
      copy at the location you choose.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
